cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a novel architecture for learning a vector representation of 3D objects that can be predicted from 2D images, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the architecture involves an autoencoder and a convolutional network, which are common components of machine learning models (cs.LG). The paper also discusses 3D model retrieval, which falls under computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of a generative model also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions voxel prediction, which is a task that involves natural language processing (cs.CL) in addition to computer vision.
